    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** headlining the roster, boasting an elite 83.29 score. His matchup against Roupp is bolstered by a significant 16% park factor advantage and an favorable 14% platoon edge, making him our primary offensive engine. Joining him at the top of the board are **Jackson Merrill** (75.10) and **Kyle Tucker** (74.98). **Jackson Merrill** benefits heavily from a high-upside matchup against Sugano (4.69 xERA) and a 17% SP skill boost, while **Kyle Tucker** remains a stable force in our two-hole, providing consistent efficiency against Rocker. **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (71.22) also projects as a strong start, as his high xwOBA of .384 helps him overcome a slight drag from the platoon disadvantage against Woods Richardson.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision today involves **Nolan Schanuel**, who narrowly missed the starting cut with a 45.66 score. While his base projection is solid, the matchup against Burns (2.76 xERA) creates too much volatility compared to our starters. We opted to prioritize the high-efficiency ceiling of **Drake Baldwin** and **Liam Hicks** at the catcher slots, both of whom carry scores near or above 60.0. Elsewhere, **Josh Lowe** presents the most risk among starters; his score of 49.16 is tethered to a brutal -19% SP skill penalty against the elite Burns. However, we are sticking with **Josh Lowe** for now, valuing his potential to capitalize on the 14% platoon edge over the bench depth provided by **Luis Robert Jr.** or **Josh Jung**, both of whom are facing difficult SP matchups that depressed their scores below our desired threshold. Managers should monitor **Heliot Ramos** and **Andy Pages** closely; while both possess solid base projections, their low-order placement limits their ceiling, though they remain viable due to the favorable stolen base environments provided by their respective matchups.",
